  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The proposed study is a two-arm, randomized, single-blinded, cross-over Phase III clinical
      trial in which patients in 3 distinct clinical scenarios will receive the 12LEG, followed by
      the standard ECG, or vice-versa. Each participant will then apply the Hand ECG themselves.
      The 3 clinical scenarios will be: 1. patients at preoperative assessment for elective cardiac
      catheterization or electrophysiology procedures; 2. patients coming for outpatient cardiology
      appointments; 3. Inpatients admitted with a cardiac diagnosis.

      The electrophysiologists reviewing ECGs will be blinded to the equipment utilized to obtain
      the ECG.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
